# docentic — agent-friendly repo scaffolder

When the user asks you to "docentic this repo" or "make this repo agent-friendly":

## Step 1 — Run the scaffold

From the repo root:

```bash
npx -y @intrepideai/docentic init
```

This creates a `docentic/template-scaffold` branch with ~50 files: `AGENTS.md` at root, a `docs/` spine (ARCHITECTURE, STACK, DATA, API, MAP, OPS, CONVENTIONS, GLOSSARY, INTEGRATIONS, SECURITY-NOTES, DECISIONS, HISTORY), `.agents/` control plane, a `research/` pipeline, and a `maintain-repo` Claude skill.

Stack detection auto-adds `docs/UI.md` / `INFRA.md` / `ML.md` / `MOBILE.md` when appropriate.

If `gh` CLI is configured, a PR opens automatically.

## Step 2 — Offer to fill the content

The scaffold leaves TODO markers in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/*.md`. Ask:

> "Scaffold done. Want me to fill in the AGENTS.md and docs/* TODOs by reading the codebase?"

If yes, fetch and follow the bootstrap prompt at:
<https://github.com/intrepideai/docentic/blob/main/prompts/bootstrap.md>

Open a follow-up PR titled `chore: populate docentic scaffold with real content`.

## Step 3 — Offer config seeding

After content is filled, ask:

> "Want me to propose research topics tailored to this codebase?"

If yes, follow:
<https://github.com/intrepideai/docentic/blob/main/prompts/config-seeder.md>

Write `research/config.proposed.yml` (don't overwrite `research/config.yml`) and open a PR.

## Hard rules

- Never modify generated files (`docs/STACK.md`, `DATA.md`, `API.md`, `MAP.md`, `INTEGRATIONS.md`) — they're owned by `scripts/llm-docs/gen-*.sh`
- Never edit anything under `scripts/llm-docs/` or `research/` infrastructure
- Never auto-merge PRs — humans review
- If the cwd isn't a git repo, tell the user to `git init` first
- If `AGENTS.md` already exists, the CLI exits cleanly — report "already scaffolded" rather than forcing

